            <h1>Cat Care Essentials</h1>
            <p>Cats are relatively low-maintenance pets but they still require proper care and attention. Here are some basic tips to help you take care of your cat:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Regular Vet Visits:</strong> Take your cat for annual check-ups and vaccinations to monitor their health.</li>
                <li><strong>Proper Nutrition:</strong> Feed your cat a diet that fits their age, health condition, and lifestyle. Always provide fresh water.</li>
                <li><strong>Litter Box Maintenance:</strong> Keep the litter box clean and odor-free. Cats are very particular about their bathroom cleanliness.</li>
                <li><strong>Scratching Posts:</strong> Provide scratching posts to help your cat maintain claw health and fulfill their scratching instincts.</li>
                <li><strong>Safe Environment:</strong> Ensure your home is safe and secure, preventing your cat from escaping or getting into harmful substances.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For further information on cat care, check out <a href="https://www.aspca.org/pet-care/cat-care">ASPCA's Cat Care Guide</a>.</p>
        </main>
